            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Hd1e108">Rubrica 8</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De experientia et vsu bellici exercitii</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="80"/>¶ De experientia et vsu bellici ex
      <lb ed="#V" n="81" break="no"/>ercitii. Rubrica. 8.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="82"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e118">SEneca de prouidentia:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e125">Ad
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>suspitionem vulne
        <lb ed="#V" n="84" break="no"/>ris tyro palescit: audacter veteranus
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>cruorem suum spectat: qui scit se se
        <lb ed="#V" n="86" break="no"/>pe vicisse post sanguinem.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e137">
               <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e136">Uegetius de re militari libro i. titulo i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e141">Inuenies ro
        <lb ed="#V" n="88" break="no"/>manos omnes gentes sola armorum exercitatione vi
        <lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>cisse. Nulla enim alia re videmus populum roma
        <lb ed="#V" n="90" break="no"/>num: orbem subegisse terrarum: nisi armorum exer <!--292.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="127-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="1" break="no"/>citio disciplina castrorum vsuque militie.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e161">
               <lb ed="#V" n="2"/>/ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e162">Libro 2. titulo 21</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e165">Semper in ocio debet fieri quod
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>necessario faciendum videtur in prelio.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e171"> 
        / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e172">22
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>titulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e173">Inexercitatus miles semper est tyro. Ue
        <lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>locitas vsu ipso acquiritur corporis: et scien
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>tia feriendi hostem seque protegendi: preser
        <lb ed="#V" n="7" break="no"/>tim si quominus dimicetur. Quemadmodum
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>bene exercitatus miles prelium cupit: ita for
        <lb ed="#V" n="9" break="no"/>midat indoctus. Sciendum est in pugna vsum
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>amplius prodesse quam vires.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e192">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e198">Cassiodorus epistolarum. libro i. epistola 39.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e196">Ars
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>bellandi si non preluditur cum fuerit neces
        <lb ed="#V" n="13" break="no"/>saria non habetur. Animos subito ad arma
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>non erigunt nisi qui se ad ipsa indoneos pre
        <lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>missa exercitatione confidunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e208"> 
        / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e214">Libro 3. epistola i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e210">Terribilis est hominibus conflictus: sit non
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>sit assiduus: et nisi vsu presumatur concertandi
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>subito fidutia non habetur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-d1e220">
               <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Rd1e230">Auctor libelli qui dicitur facetus. capitulo 10. et finali.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98929-Qd1e224">Sepius insolito pugna nocere solet.</quote>
            </p>
